Name: Notes
Children Under 6 Years with Elevated Blo:
Rates are calculated by using the number of children less than 6 years old tested in a given year with blood lead levels of 5 mcg/dL or 10 mcg/dL or greater, divided by the number of children less than 6 years old who were tested for lead poisoning in a given year; expressed as cases per 1,000 tested.
Children can receive more than one test during the calendar year, but are only counted once using the highest confirmed blood lead level during the calendar year.
